docs.abstract: The president has made “executing babies” part of his refrain on abortion, but the evidence does not back him up.
docs.snippet: The president has made “executing babies” part of his refrain on abortion, but the evidence does not back him up.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump revived on Saturday night what is fast becoming a standard, and inaccurate, refrain about doctors “executing babies.” During a more than hourlong speech at a rally in Green Bay, Wis., Mr. Trump admonished the Democratic governor, Tony Evers, for vetoing a Republican bill that could send doctors to prison for life if they fail to give medical care to children born alive after a failed abortion attempt.

headline.main: Trump Repeats a False Claim That Doctors ‘Execute’ Newborns
